data.name: label9.Text
data.value: If you need to delete all backups, click the button below. CAREFUL! This is irreversible.

data.name: EnableSnapshotCheckbox.Text
data.value: Keep only one backup. Replace the older ones with new. (Reccomended for in use with a cloud storage client)

data.name: label7.Text
data.value: This is where the save files will be automatically backed up. For safety reasons, they will be saved in different folders named after the date and time of the backup.

data.name: AutoBackupCheckbox.Text
data.value: Automatically backup my save files. When enabled, the launcher will automatically backup your save files to a folder of your choosing. It is recommended that is used in conjuction with a cloud storage service (for example, OneDrive).

data.name: DeleteFailedLabel.Text
data.value: Failed to delete the save files!

data.name: DeleteAllSavesCheckBox.Text
data.value: I understand and I want to use it.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value: This will delete all save files thus you'll lose all your progress. This is irreversible. Use this ONLY if you need it (for example, all your save files are corrupt).

data.name: label3.Text
data.value: This will export your save files to a folder of your choosing. Select it from the folder picker and it will export them automatically.

data.name: SlotSelectCheckBox.Text
data.value: Set it to the following save slot:

data.name: label1.Text
data.value: This will import a save file of your choice to the game's save folder. Select it from the file picker and it will be imported automatically. WARNING! This will replace the save file with the same name.

data.name: BackupFolderPicker.Description
data.value: Where shall I back up you save files to?

data.name: RestoreFolderPicker.Description
data.value: Select the folder of the backup you want to restore. Their name is something like this: BackupYYYYMMDDHHmm.

data.name: ExportFilePicker.Title
data.value: Select the files to export (WARNING: DO NOT LEAVE THE FOLDER!)
